Stop scrolling, turn your sound on and take a seat!

Join @hannahbarrettyoga and I for this short meditation to find your Sunday calm!

📣EXCITING ANNOUNCMENT📣

You can also join us both LIVE on the MAIN STAGE at @wanderlustgb 108 London

💙Battersea Park 
💜July 31st
❤️Link to join in person OR virtually in my bio @maudehirst 

Tickets are selling fast BUT there are still some available. So jump in quick! We’re SOOOO EXCITED!

If you like me are craving some community and connection, this event is going to be MAGIC ✨

Comment below how this meditation makes you feel👇

#wanderlust108
#festival
#backtogether
#energyrise

I recently had the honour of asking one of the greatest living spiritual teachers @sadhguru a question.

As you know, my mission is to make mindfulness accessible to as many people as I can, so I asked a question I thought may be helpful to those just beginning on their spiritual journey.

I will let the video do all the speaking for itself.

Thank you so much to @sadhguru and @isha_USA for getting me involved 💜

#RideWithSadhguru
#energyrise
#sadhguru

node.text:
When the world feels unpredictable it’s easy to fall into thought patterns of worrying about the future or wanting to recreate the past. Neither of these thoughts are useful because we can’t change the past or future. All we really have is this present moment✨
And in the present moment worry disappears and we can feel peaceful!

How do you get present?🤷🏼‍♀️

The way to bring yourself back into the PRESENT is by reconnecting to the breath and body. This guided meditation will bring you there 🧘🏼‍♀️

My members club for the mind opens for enrolment at 4pm UK tomorrow. Come and workout your mind back to the peaceful present moment. 
Join the VIP waiting list to be the first to gain access- link in my bio @maudehirst

#themembersclubforthemind
#bepresent

node.text:
As we slowly come out of lockdown I have been hearing from lots of you that you’re experiencing anxiety and stress. 

When we feel anxiety in the body, without knowing it the breath gets short and shallow and this can lead to a deeper state of anxiety. The way to counteract these feelings is to bring awareness to your breath, deepening and slowing down the pace of the breath. 

2 breathing techniques that will help:

1- bring your hands to the side of the rib cage and breath into the hands - expanding outwards on the inhale for the count of 4 and softening on the exhale for the count of 4

2- Coherent breathing. Simply breath in and out of the nose for 6 seconds. Regulating the breath brings your body into a state of calm and balance

Try these breathing techniques for 10 minutes in the mornings to start your day from a place of calm. Or whenever you are feeling anxious.

✨SURRENDER✨

This week with my members and in my own personal practices, I have been focussing on the idea of surrendering. 

So often in life we try to fight against what we’re feeling…
😴when we’re tired, we fight against the tiredness
😢when we’re sad, we fight back the tears
🥳when we feel really excited we often play down the joy 

In resisting how we truly feel, it can often cause us to suffer more. However, if we learn to surrender into what IS happening rather than what we want to happen, life begins to feel in flow and easy.

So let yourself FEEL and SURRENDER to what it is you are truly feeling. Flow with life rather than against it ✨

🧘🏼‍♀️”I’m too busy to meditate”🧘🏼‍♀️

What stops you from meditating?🛑

- my mind is too busy
- I don’t have the time
- I’m not the right kind of person
- It’s too woo woo for me
- I don’t want to sit with myself in fear of what I’ll discover 

Comment below with what puts you off starting 👇

Even though we know meditation has now been proven to help with our mental health, there is still lots of resistance around starting. I would love to hear from you so that I can offer solutions to your meditation worries.

🧘🏼‍♀️It wasn’t made for a select personality type, it was created to empower each and every one of us.

💖You don’t have to be zen to start - you just need to commit to trying💖

#energyrise
#meditationwithmaude
#meditationapp

🌊Happy World Ocean’s Day 🌊

Let's celebrate in the best way possible: BEING ACTIVIST ⛔️

8 milion tonnes of plastic flow into the oceans every year and it’s our responsibility to become aware of the small difference we can individually make to help this figure reduce.

@wedo_act (the natural and eco-ethical hair care brand) have inspired me to become much more conscious of the products I am choosing PLUS to BE ACTIVIST by getting out to the water around me (in London), to start collecting some of this plastic before it reaches the oceans and YOU 👇 CAN DO THE SAME!

Join me in making a better world:
💜 Become conscious of the plastic you are using and find eco-ethical brands like @wedo_act - who with every product sold, partner with @plasticbank to remove 8 plastic bottles from the environment 
💙 Get out and pick up all the plastic you see 🗑

Comment below to share how you’re getting involved and tag your friends too 👇

#TogetherWeDo
#weDoers
#WorldOceansDay
#ad
